{"questionId":"32404605","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In this question, all distances are in kilometres and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> is in hours.<br>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> be a displacement of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math> due east, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> be a displacement of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math> due north, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>1</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math> be a vertical displacement of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>km</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Highway 85 in Saudi Arabia is a long, straight, flat road.</p>\n<p>Relative to the centre of the town Arar, point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>, the position vector of a car, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi></math>, travelling along this road is given by:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mover><mi>OC</mi><mo>→</mo></mover><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>10</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>t</mi><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>50</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo>-</mo><mn>33</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>0</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>.</p></div>\n<di